• Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above. ENGCOBO - Police Minister Fikile Mbalula shed more light on the shootout between police and suspects on Friday night at eNgcobo in the Eastern Cape. Mbalula said the church where the suspects were found is a place where satanism is practiced. Mbalula, together with the National Police Commissioner General Khehla Sitole, briefed the community on the developments following the shooting. Mbalula said the suspects were arrested within 65 hours of the allocated 72 hours given to find the suspects. Seven suspects were killed in the shootout while a police officer was wounded. READ: Seven eNgcobo murder suspects killed in shootout with police Parliament's police portfolio committee welcomed the arrest of 10 suspects and the confiscation of a large number of weapons. The small town in the Eastern Cape has been left reeling after assailants entered a police station and opened fire on officers. Five policemen and a retired soldier were killed. eNCA